This paper deals with deep learning methods applied to medical image analysis, specifically lung nodule malignancy classification. The paper proposes a novel interpretable deep hierarchical semantic convolutional neural network (HSCNN) to predict whether a given pulmonary nodule observed on a computed tomography (CT) scan is malignant. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with deep learning models that are difficult to interpret and do not incorporate prior domain knowledge, which suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also uses the Lung Image Database Consortium (LIDC) dataset, which suggests that it may belong to the Medical Imaging (cs.MS) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image analysis, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
